{"parents": [{"link": "../", "title": "Release notes"}], "prev": {"link": "../3.1.8/", "title": "Django 3.1.8 release notes"}, "next": {"link": "../3.1.6/", "title": "Django 3.1.6 release notes"}, "title": "Django 3.1.7 release notes", "meta": {}, "body": "<div class=\"section\" id=\"s-django-3-1-7-release-notes\">\n<span id=\"django-3-1-7-release-notes\"></span><h1>Django 3.1.7 release notes<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#django-3-1-7-release-notes\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h1>\n<p><em>February 19, 2021</em></p>\n<p>Django 3.1.7 fixes a security issue and a bug in 3.1.6.</p>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"s-cve-2021-23336-web-cache-poisoning-via-django-utils-http-limited-parse-qsl\">\n<span id=\"cve-2021-23336-web-cache-poisoning-via-django-utils-http-limited-parse-qsl\"></span><h2>CVE-2021-23336: Web cache poisoning via <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">django.utils.http.limited_parse_qsl()</span></code><a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#cve-2021-23336-web-cache-poisoning-via-django-utils-http-limited-parse-qsl\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<p>Django contains a copy of <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/urllib.parse.html#urllib.parse.parse_qsl\" title=\"(in Python v3.11)\"><code class=\"xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">urllib.parse.parse_qsl()</span></code></a> which was added to\nbackport some security fixes. A further security fix has been issued recently\nsuch that <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">parse_qsl()</span></code> no longer allows using <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">;</span></code> as a query parameter\nseparator by default. Django now includes this fix. See <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://bugs.python.org/issue?&#64;action=redirect&amp;bpo=42967\">bpo-42967</a> for\nfurther details.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"s-bugfixes\">\n<span id=\"bugfixes\"></span><h2>Bugfixes<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#bugfixes\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">\u00b6</a></h2>\n<ul class=\"simple\">\n<li>Fixed a regression in Django 3.1 that caused <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">RuntimeError</span></code> instead of\nconnection errors when using only the <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">'postgres'</span></code> database\n(<a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://code.djangoproject.com/ticket/32403\">#32403</a>).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n", "metatags": "", "rellinks": [["genindex", "General Index", "I", "index"], ["py-modindex", "Python Module Index", "", "modules"], ["releases/3.1.6", "Django 3.1.6 release notes", "N", "next"], ["releases/3.1.8", "Django 3.1.8 release notes", "P", "previous"]], "sourcename": "releases/3.1.7.txt", "toc": "<ul>\n<li><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"#\">Django 3.1.7 release notes</a><ul>\n<li><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"#cve-2021-23336-web-cache-poisoning-via-django-utils-http-limited-parse-qsl\">CVE-2021-23336: Web cache poisoning via <code class=\"docutils literal notranslate\"><span class=\"pre\">django.utils.http.limited_parse_qsl()</span></code></a></li>\n<li><a class=\"reference internal\" href=\"#bugfixes\">Bugfixes</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n", "display_toc": true, "page_source_suffix": ".txt", "current_page_name": "releases/3.1.7", "sidebars": ["localtoc.html", "relations.html", "sourcelink.html", "searchbox.html"], "customsidebar": null, "favicon_url": null, "logo_url": null, "alabaster_version": "0.7.13", "include_console_assets": false}